arch:property.oc:show_val: Opening elevation: 904.926 m at southwest; Elevation controls: 905.346 m on P/ST 573, Stylobate stone and 905.566 m on P/ST 581.
Associated with: Trenches 1 and 2 Stylobate, built-up to the Easternmost Porch (Artie) column on the west.
Closing elevation: 904.676 m at center stair, 904.146 m at northwest (P/ST 574; stair east 904.446 m, step above drain 904.246 m, drain 904.106 m).

Phase XIV: Modern period marked by Bedouin activity and the accumulation of recent debris. Nazzal's dump is dug between the collapsed Porch columns on the temple Forecourt. A German survey between the temple stylobate and Forecourt results in the disturbance of these deposits.

Clean-up north of the Stylobate, consists of rubble, sterile sand and plaster lump debris of a previous excavation dump. Soil is light brown (Munsell 7.5YR 6/4) with one very dark gray, ashy deposit (Munsell 7.5YR 4/1) at 904.446 m. One object was cataloged: a corroded iron clamp (93-M-2).
